 and Mattholomule to detention as well where it's revealed to be a giant pit with worm creatures that entrap students in brainwashing bubbles to make them good. Luz and Gus escape with Mattholomule just in time to run into Bump and Eda. After calling off the worm creatures, Bump kicks out Luz. Gus takes the blame and he is removed from the H.A.S. as president and member altogether. And with Luz also kicked out of the club, Mattholomule becomes the new president, seeing as he's \"still alive.\" Eda tells Luz that she's allowing her into Hexside because she knows that she's smart enough to make her own decisions as well as Bump agreeing to not to tell the Emperor's Coven about their deal. In the final scene, Luz reads every mischief that Eda did as she mentions that Bump was right about her.\n| LineColor       = FADA5E\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 10\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 10\n| Title           = Escape of the Palisman\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|3|20}}\n| DirectedBy      = Aminder Dhaliwal\n| WrittenBy       = {{StoryTeleplay|s=Dana Terrace|t=John Bailey Owen, Terrace & Rachel Vine}}\n| Aux2            = Inbal Breda, Bosook \"Bo\" Coburn, Dhaliwal, Ben Holm & Amelia Lorenz\n| ProdCode        = 108\n| Viewers         = 0.52<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-friday-cable-originals-network-finals-3-20-2020.html|title=SHOWBUZZDAILY's Top 150 Friday Cable Originals\u00a0& Network Finals: 3.20.2020 {{!}} Showbuzz Daily|website=www.showbuzzdaily.com|access-date=2020-03-23}}</ref>\n| ShortSummary    = When Eda begins to feel the effects of her curse, she decides to take a rest. Luz meets up with Willow and Gus to see a grudgby match between Hexside and Glandus. They miss the bus, so Luz decides to use Eda's staff. They fly and end up crashing into a tree, resulting in Owlbert cracking his head and running from Luz. The kids run into the Bat Queen who is protecting Owlbert and gives Luz a series of trials to win Owlbert's trust back. King discovers that Eda is in her cursed form, but is more docile. He decides to use her to get revenge on the children at the park, but this alerts animal control, the former demon hunters, who take Eda away. He tries to use the elixir on her, but it has no effect. Knowing it's Eda's favorite thing for him to do, he squeals and it turns Eda back to normal. After completing the tasks, the Bat Queen refuses to give up Owlbert. Luz discovers that the Bat Queen was a palisman to a giant and has been protecting other palismans. Realizing that Owlbert trusts Luz now, she lets him go. As everyone heads home, Eda realizes that the elixir is not working well enough.\n| LineColor       = FADA5E\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 11\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 11\n| Title           = Adventures in the Elements\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|TBA}}{{efn|name=ep111|This episode made its broadcast premiere on April 17, 2020 in Turkey.}}\n| DirectedBy      = Sabrina Cotugno\n| WrittenBy       = {{StoryTeleplay|s=Charley Feldman, Zach Marcus, John Bailey Owen, Dana Terrace & Rachel Vine|t=John Bailey Owen & Dana Terrace}}\n| Aux2            = Inbal Breda, Emmy Cicierega, Cotugno, Madeleine Flores & Chris Pianka\n| ProdCode        = \n| Viewers         = \n| ShortSummary    = \n| LineColor       = FADA5E\n}}\n}}\n\n===Shorts===\n====''Look Hooo's Talking''====\nA series of shorts, modeled after the [[aftershow]] format, titled ''Look Hooo's Talking'' premiered on the official YouTube channel for Disney Channel. The shorts, which are usually posted a day after an episode's airing but air right after its TV premiere, depict two live action owls named Horus Herashoo and Owlyvia Kim talking about the events of the most recent episode and pick apart some of the details that potentially will make an impact later in the show. At the end of each episode, the credits quickly scroll by, but when paused reveal the name of the \"crew\" which consists of names of the actual crew of the show, but with reimagined bird name puns such as the creator, Dana Terrace, being renamed Danightigale Terrace.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=J5BoeNlsQZ8|title=Episode 1 {{!}} Look Hooo's Talking {{!}} The Owl House {{!}} Disney Channel|website=YouTube|publisher=Disney Channel|date=January 11, 2020}}</ref>\n\n====''Owl Pellets''====\nDisney Channel began releasing a series of comedic shorts involving Luz, Eda and King's antics with magic and the exploration of the Boiling Isles.\n{{Episode table\n| total_width     = \n| background      = #000\n| overall         = 10\n| title           = \n| airdate         = 30\n| airdateT        = Online release date\n| episodes        =\n\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 1\n| Title           = Welcome to Hexside!\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|2020|4|4}}<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5Kd0NIn9Y7k|title=Welcome to Hexside! \ud83d\udd2e{{!}} Owl Pellets {{!}} The Owl House {{!}} Disney Channel|website=YouTube|publisher=Disney Channel|date=April 4, 2020}}</ref>\n| ShortSummary    = Principal Bump welcomes you to Hexside School of Magic and Demonics! Their top priority is keeping students safe, providing amazing food in the cafeteria, and giving students the support they need!\n| LineColor       = 000\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 2\n| Title           = Eda's Cursed Brush\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|2020|4|11}}<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=PAmpT_1Jjns|title=Eda's Cursed Brush \ud83d\ude08{{!}} Owl Pellets {{!}} The Owl House {{!}} Disney Channel|website=YouTube|publisher=Disney Channel|date=April 11, 2020}}</ref>\n| ShortSummary    = Luz teaches Eda how to make fine art out of anything! But when Luz uses Eda's cursed pencil, things go awry!\n| LineColor       = 000\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 3\n| Title           = Paint Scare!\n| OriginalAirDate = {{start date|2020|4|18}}<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=h3zQbicMMx8|title=Paint Scare! \ud83d\ude31{{!}} Owl Pellets {{!}} The Owl House {{!}} Disney Channel|website=YouTube|publisher=Disney Channel|date=April 18, 2020}}</ref>\n| ShortSummary    = Luz and King head off to the woods to paint scenic nature! But they can't seem to escape a dark mysterious figure in their painting! \n| LineColor       = 000\n}}\n}}\n{{reflist|group=lower-alpha}}\n\n==Production==\n''The Owl House'' was created by Dana Terrace, previously a storyboard artist for ''[[Gravity Falls]]'' and later a director on the 2017 ''[[DuckTales (2017 TV series)|DuckTales]]'' reboot. The series was set originally for a 2019 release,<ref name=Deadline2018 /> but it was delayed for a 2020 release.<ref name=DisneyABCPress/><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://mobile.twitter.com/DanaTerrace/status/1109165637778051072|title=Dana Terrace on Twitter|access-date=April 29, 2019}}</ref> Terrace is the fourth woman to create a series for [[Disney Television Animation]], after ''[[Pepper Ann]]'' with [[Sue Rose]], ''[[Doc McStuffins]]'' with [[Chris Nee]], and ''[[Star vs. the Forces of Evil]]'' with Daron Nefcy.\n\nThe show is animated by [[Rough Draft Korea]], [[Sunmin Image Pictures]], and Sugarcube Animation.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/BtQn3amnsiO/|title=Dana Terrace on Instagram|access-date=April 29, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://mobile.twitter.com/DanaTerrace/status/1108100342426681344|title=Dana Terrace on Twitter|access-date=}}</ref> Terrace said that the visual style was inspired by paintings by [[Remedios Varo]], [[John Bauer (illustrator)|John Bauer]] and [[Hieronymus Bosch]], as well as Russian architecture.<ref name=\"oneofus\">{{Cite web|url=https://oneofus.net/2019/06/infestation-annecy-animation-festival-2019-the-owl-house/|title=Infestation: Annecy Animation Festival 2019: The Owl House|first=Chris|last=Cox|date=Jun 27, 2019|website=One of Us|access-date=Aug 25, 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn November 21, 2019, the show was renewed for a second season prior to the first season's debut.<ref name=\"S2\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/disney-channels-owl-house-gets-early-season-2-order-1256811|title=Disney Channel's 'The Owl House' Gets Season 2 Order Ahead of Series Premiere (Exclusive)|first=Kimberly|last=Nordyke|date=November 21, 2019|website=The Hollywood Reporter|access-date=November 21, 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Marketing===\nOn June 10, 2019, the trailer premiered during the show's Annecy 2019 panel. It was later uploaded to Disney Channel's YouTube channel a day later.<ref name=\"LAT-trailer\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.latimes.com/entertainment/herocomplex/la-et-hc-owl-house-first-trailer-20190611-story.html|title=Watch 'The Owl House' first-look trailer|work=[[Los Angeles Times]]|date=June 11, 2019|access-date=July 5, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"oneofus\"/>\n\nThe show's main title sequence was released on July 19, 2019, during [[San Diego Comic-Con]] 2019.<ref>{{Cite tweet|user=DisneyTVA|number=1152299626898317312|date=19 July 2019|title=Step inside the magical portal, and enjoy the just-released Main Title for #TheOwlHouse!|access-date=July 22, 2019}}</ref>\n\nThe show released a sneak peek and an official end credit sequence on October 4, 2019, during a panel at [[New York Comic Con]] 2019.\n\n==Reception==\n===Critical reception===\n''The Owl House'' has received a positive reception from critics. Emily Ashby of ''[[Common Sense Media]]'' said putting different elements together made the series quirky and likable. It was also described as well written and animated, and speculated that \"(the show) likely will be one you will want to watch alongside your older kids and tweens, giving you the opportunity to discuss these kinds of themes as they come up.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.commonsensemedia.org/tv-reviews/the-owl-house|title=The Owl House TV Review|website=[[Common Sense Media]]|first=Emily|last=Ashby|date=January 10, 2020|access-date=January 12, 2020|language=en}}</ref> ''LaughingPlace.com''{{'}}s critic praised the series for its unique visuals and voice acting, stating \"The performances fit together beautifully as the diversity in their delivery showcases the characters\u2019 unique roles in the Demon Realm.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.laughingplace.com/w/articles/2020/01/09/tv-review-the-owl-house-brings-the-demon-realm-to-disney-channel/|title=TV Review: \"The Owl House\" Brings the Demon Realm to Disney Channel|website=LaughingPlace.com|date=January 9, 2020|access-date=January 12, 2020|language=en}}</ref> ''[[Collider (website)|Collider]]''{{'}}s Dave Trumbore gave the series' first episode a 4-star rating, feeling that the episode \"[has] got a dark, yet darkly comic edge to the whole thing.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://collider.com/owl-house-disney-review/|title='The Owl House' Review: Magic, Mythology & the Most Intriguing Lore Since 'Gravity Falls'|website=[[Collider (website)|Collider]]|first=Dave|last=Trumbore|date=January 8, 2020|access-date=January 12, 2020|language=en}}</ref>\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Official website|https://disneynow.go.com/shows/the-owl-house/}}\n*{{IMDb title|8050756}}\n{{Disney Channel Original Series}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Owl House, The (Tv series)}}\n[[Category:2020s American animated television series]]\n[[Category:2020 American television series debuts]]\n[[Category:American children's animated adventure television series]]\n[[Category:American children's animated comedy television series]]\n[[Category:American children's animated fantasy television series]]\n[[Category:Anime-influenced Western animated television series]]\n[[Category:English-language television programs]]\n[[Category:Disney Channel original programming]]\n[[Category:Television series by Disney Television Animation]]\n[[Category:Animated television series about teenagers]]\n[[Category:Witchcraft in television]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Disney animated TV series, 2020}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name                = The Owl House\n| image                    = The Owl House intro.png\n| genre                    = {{Plainlist|\n*[[Comedy]]<ref name=\"CharacterNames\" />\n*[[Fantasy]]<ref name=\"CharacterNames\" />\n}}\n| creator                  = Dana Terrace\n| developer                = \n| writer                   = \n| director                 = \n| voices                   = Sarah-Nicole Robles<br>[[Wendie Malick]]<br>[[Alex Hirsch]]\n| composer                 = T.J. Hill<ref>{{cite tweet|user=DanaTerrace|first=Dana|last=Terrace|date=July 19, 2019|number=1152331341876215809|title=I\u2019m going to give a full credits list for the Main Titles soon but just wanted to give a special shout out to @tjhill for composing a ROCKIN theme song, can\u2019t wait for you guys to hear what he\u2019s doing for the show. So lucky to have him as our composer!!!|access-date=July 22, 2019}}</ref>\n| country                  = United States\n| language                 = English\n| num_seasons              = 1\n| num_episodes             = 10\n| list_episodes            = #Episodes\n| executive_producer       = Dana Terrace\n| producer                 = Wade Wisinski<br>Stephen Sandoval (supervising producer)\n| editor                   = Kevin Locarro<br>Jenny Jordan (assistant editor)<br>Rachel Vine (story editor)\n| runtime                  = 22 minutes\n| company                  = [[Disney Television Animation]]\n| distributor              = [[Disney-ABC Domestic Television]]\n| network                  = [[Disney Channel]]<br />[[Disney XD]]\n| picture_format           = [[1080p]] ([[16:9]] [[HDTV]])\n| website                  = https://disneynow.go.com/shows/the-owl-house/\n| website_title            = Official website\n| image_alt                = \n| caption                  = \n| channel                  = \n| first_aired              = January 10, 2020\n| last_aired               = {{End date|present}}\n}}\n\n'''''The Owl House''''' is an American animated fantasy-comedy television series produced by [[Disney Television Animation]]. The series was created by Dana Terrace, and premiered on [[Disney Channel]] on January 10, 2020.<ref name=DisneyABCPress>{{cite web|url=https://www.disneyabcpress.com/disneychannel/shows/the-owl-house/|title=The Owl House {{!}} Disney Channel Press|publisher=DisneyABC Press|access-date=March 11, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"LAT-trailer\"/><ref>{{cite web|author=Disney Channel|title=New York Comic-Con Sneak Peek! {{!}} The Owl House {{!}} Disney Channel|url= https://m.youtube.com/watch?v=JC3TiGmIwdY|website=YouTube|date=October 4, 2019}}</ref> In November 2019, the show was renewed for a second season in advance of the first season's premiere.<ref name=\"S2\" />\n\n==Plot==\nLuz is a teenage human girl who accidentally stumbles upon a portal to another world instead of going to Reality Check Camp. When on the Boiling Isles, which is made from the remains of a dead Titan, she befriends the rebellious witch Eda the Owl Lady and an adorable demon warrior named King. Despite not having [[Magic (supernatural)|magical]] abilities and having to pose as a witch due to the prejudice towards humans, Luz pursues her dream of becoming a witch by serving as Eda's apprentice at the Owl House and ultimately finds a new family in an unlikely setting.<ref name=Deadline2018>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2018/02/disney-channel-renews-star-vs-the-forces-of-evil-announces-amphibia-owl-house-1202300438/|title=Disney Channel Launching Toon Series 'Amphibia' & 'The Owl House', Renews 'Star Vs. The Forces Of Evil' For Season 4|work=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date=February 23, 2018|access-date=July 5, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Cast==\n===Main===\n* Sarah-Nicole Robles as Luz Noceda,<ref name=\"CharacterNames\">{{cite web|url=https://www.wdtvpress.com/disneychannel/pressrelease/owl-house-s1-fact-sheet/|title=Owl House: S1 Fact Sheet|website=Disney ABC Press|date=November 21, 2019|access-date=January 2, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author=Disney Channel|title=Official Trailer \ud83c\udfa5 {{!}} The Owl House {{!}} Disney Channel|url= https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1W1FFiT51lg|website=YouTube|date=January 3, 2019}}</ref> a 14-year-old [[Dominican-American]]<ref>{{cite news |last1=Elderkin |first1=Beth |title=The Personal Story Behind Owl House's Magical New Disney Heroine |url=https://io9.gizmodo.com/the-personal-story-behind-owl-houses-magical-new-disney-1839128407 |accessdate=February 19, 2020 |work=[[io9]] |date=October 17, 2019}}</ref> girl who ends up on the Boiling Isles and becomes both Eda's apprentice and a new exchange student at Hexside Academy. Luz loves all things fantasy and magical, wishing to become a witch.<ref name=\"S2\" />\n* [[Wendie Malick]] as Edalyn \"Eda\" Clawthorne,<ref name=\"CharacterNames\" /> the most powerful witch on the Boiling Isles, Luz's teacher, and a [[Bounty (reward)|wanted criminal]] for selling human items and not joining a coven.<ref name=\"S2\" /> Her nickname \"the Owl Lady\" comes from the fact that she was cursed to become an owl-like monster when she was younger by an unknown figure, which can only be countered by a daily elixir, which is gradually losing its effect on her as she revealed the curse is getting stronger as time passes. In mid-season finale, the elixir has lost its effect altogether due to the curse having grown too powerful. It can no longer cure her, much to her shock and fear.\n* [[Alex Hirsch]] as King,<ref name=\"CharacterNames\" /> a small dog-like demon warrior and Eda's roommate who is the self-proclaimed King of Demons.\n** Hirsch also voices Hooty, the witty sentient [[barn owl]]-headed [[doorknocker]] of the titular house.<ref name=\"S2\" />\n\n===Recurring===\n* [[Tati Gabrielle]] as Willow,<ref name=\"CharacterNames\" /> a student at Hexside and Luz and Gus\u2019s friend who can do plant magic. Originally, Willow was placed in the abomination class until her use of plant magic caused her to be transferred to the plant class.\n* [[Issac Ryan Brown]] as Gus,<ref name=\"CharacterNames\" /> a student at Hexside and Luz and Willow\u2019s friend who can do illusion magic. He once led a human-appreciation club called the Human Appreciation Society before he was removed from the position by Principal Bump after what happened to the detention room.\n* [[Mae Whitman]] as Amity Blight,<ref name=\"CharacterNames\" /> a top student at Hexside who is an abomination expert and Luz's rival.\n* [[Bumper Robinson]] as Hieronymus Bump,<ref name=\"CharacterNames\" /> the principal of Hexside who wears a demon-shaped hat over half his face.\n* [[JB Blanc]] as Professor Abominable, a teacher who teaches students how to make abominations and is carried around Hexside by his own Abomination.\n* Dana Terrace as Tiny Nose, a small round creature with a prominent nose.\n* [[Cissy Jones]] as Lilith Clawthorne, Eda's sister and leader of the Emperor's Coven.\n* [[Parvesh Cheena]] as Tiblit Tibley \"Tibbles\" Grimhammer III,<ref name=\"CharacterNames\" /> a night market stand owner who supplies Eda's curse elixir.\n* [[Eden Riegel]] as Boscha,<ref name=\"CharacterNames\" /> a three-eyed witch who is Amity's friend and is obsessed with Penstagram.\n* [[Isabella Rossellini]] as the Bat Queen, a former palisman formerly owned by a giant that takes care of other forgotten palismans and her kids.\n\n===Guest===\n*[[Matthew Rhys]]<ref name=\"S2\" />\n\n==Episodes==\n===Season 1 (2020)===\n\n{{Episode table\n| background      =  #FADA5E\n| overall         = \n| season          = \n| title           = \n| titleR          = \n| airdate         = \n| DirectedBy      =\n| WrittenBy       =\n| airdateR        = \n| aux2=\n| aux2T=Storyboarded by\n| prodcode        = \n| prodcodeR       = <ref name=\"WDTV Press Episode Info\">{{Cite web|url= https://www.wdtvpress.com/disneychannel/shows/the-owl-house/episodes/ |title=WDTV Press Episode Info|access-date=January 11, 2020}}</ref>\n| viewers         =\n