nest Augustus, King of Hanover|Ernest Augustus]] }}\n|-\n{{s-off}}\n{{s-bef | before = [[Robert Dundas, 2nd Viscount Melville|The Viscount Melville]] | as = [[First Lord of the Admiralty]]| }}\n{{s-ttl | title = [[Lord High Admiral of the United Kingdom|Lord High Admiral]] | years = 1827\u20131828 }}\n{{s-aft | after = [[Robert Dundas, 2nd Viscount Melville|The Viscount Melville]] | as = [[First Lord of the Admiralty]] }}\n{{s-hon}}\n{{s-bef | before = [[Prince Frederick, Duke of York and Albany|The Duke of York and Albany]] }}\n{{s-ttl | title = [[Great Master of the Order of the Bath]] | years = 1827\u20131830 }}\n{{s-vac | next = [[Prince Augustus Frederick, Duke of Sussex|The Duke of Sussex]] }}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{English, Scottish and British monarchs}}\n{{Rulers of Hanover}}\n{{British princes}}\n{{Hanoverian princes}}\n{{Dukes of Clarence}}\n{{Grand Masters of the Order of the Bath}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2018}}\n{{Use British English|date=October 2012}}\n{{Featured article}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:William 04 Of The United Kingdom}}\n[[Category:William IV of the United Kingdom| ]]\n[[Category:1765 births]]\n[[Category:1837 deaths]]\n[[Category:18th-century British people]]\n[[Category:19th-century British monarchs]]\n[[Category:18th-century Royal Navy personnel]]\n[[Category:19th-century Royal Navy personnel]]\n[[Category:Royal Navy personnel of the American Revolutionary War]]\n[[Category:Burials at St George's Chapel, Windsor Castle]]\n[[Category:Dukes of Clarence]]\n[[Category:Peers of Great Britain created by George III]]\n[[Category:Earls of Munster]]\n[[Category:Peers of Ireland created by George III]]\n[[Category:Fellows of the Society of Antiquaries of London]]\n[[Category:Great Masters of the Order of the Bath]]\n[[Category:Hanoverian princes]]\n[[Category:Kings of Hanover]]\n[[Category:Knights of the Garter]]\n[[Category:Knights of the Thistle]]\n[[Category:Lord High Admirals]]\n[[Category:Members of the Privy Council of Grea