      = <!-- Should not be used to indicate a program that preceded another in a television lineup. -->\n| followed_by          = <!-- Should not be used to indicate a program that followed another in a television lineup. -->\n| related              = {{ubl|[[Mother (Japanese TV series)|''Mother'']] (Japan)|''[[Anne (Turkish TV series)|Anne]]'' (Turkey)}}\n| website              = http://program.tving.com/tvn/mother/\n}}\n\n'''''Mother'''''<ref>{{cite video|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=SyK7vR2VD-k|title=Mother \uc544\uc774\uac00 \ub2e4\uccd0\ub3c4 '\ubb34\ub364\ub364'\ud55c \uc5c4\ub9c8 \uace0\uc131\ud76c, \uc0c1\ud669\uc744 \uc54c\uac8c \ub41c \uc774\ubcf4\uc601 180124 EP.1|website=YouTube|publisher=tvN Drama|accessdate=January 25, 2018|language=ko}}</ref> ({{Korean|\ub9c8\ub354||Madeo}}) is a 2018 [[Korean drama|South Korean television series]] starring [[Lee Bo-young]], [[Heo Yool]] and [[Lee Hye-young (actress, born 1962)|Lee Hye-young]]. It is a remake of the award-winning [[Mother (Japanese TV series)|2010 Japanese TV series of the same title]]. It aired on [[TVN (South Korean TV channel)|tvN]]'s Wednesdays and Thursdays at 21:30 ([[Time in South Korea|KST]]) time slot from January 24 to March 15, 2018.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.broadcastingcable.com/thewire/nippon-tv-announces-deal-cj-em-korean-format-its-award-winning-japanese-drama-series-mother/169388|title=Nippon TV Announces Deal with CJ E&M for Korean format of its Award-winning Japanese Drama Series \"Mother\"|website=Broadcasting & Cable|publisher=NewBay Media|accessdate=December 14, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.hancinema.net/actress-lee-bo-young-will-be-playing-another-strong-willed-mother-role-in-2018-108263.html|title=Actress Lee Bo-young Will Be Playing Another Strong-willed Mother Role in 2018|website=Hancinema|publisher=TV Report|accessdate=December 14, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Kim|first1=Jeong-yeon|url=http://www.sisunnews.co.kr/news/articleView.html?idxno=71599|script-title=ko:\ucc28\uac00\uc6b4 \uad50\uc0ac\ub85c \uc644\ubcbd \ubab0\uc785\ud55c '\ub9c8\ub354'\uc774\ubcf4\uc601, \ubb34\ud45c\uc815\ud55c \ubaa8\uc2b5 \uc720\uc9c0|website=Sisun News|publisher=Sisun News|accessdate=December 14, 2017|language=ko}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://english.yonhapnews.co.kr/kwave/2018/01/18/3001000000AEN20180118010900315.html|title=New TV series 'Mother' calls attention to motherhood, child abuse|accessdate=January 18, 2018|website=Yonhap News|publisher=Yonhap News Agency}}</ref>\n\n==Synopsis==\nA temporary teacher at an elementary school realizes that one of her students is being abused at home by her family. She makes an impulsive decision to kidnap the child and attempts to become her mother.\n\n==Cast==\n===Main===\n* [[Lee Bo-young]] as Kang Soo-jin; Yoon-Bok\u2019s teacher, and soon adopted mother \n* [[Heo Yool]] as Kim Hye-na (changed to Kim Yoon-bok); one of Soo-jin\u2019s students, and soon adopted daughter\n* [[Lee Hye-young (actress, born 1962)|Lee Hye-young]] as Young-sin; Soo Jin, Yi-jin, and Hyun-Jin\u2019s adoptive mother\n**[[Choi Yoon-so]] as young Young-sin\n\n===Supporting===\n====People around Soo-jin====\n* [[Lee Jae-yoon]] as Jin-hong\n* [[Kim Young-jae (actor, born 1975)|Kim Young-jae]] as Eun-cheol\n*Nam Ki-ae as Nam Hong-hee; Soo-jin\u2019s birth mother\n\n====People around Yoon-bok ====\n* [[Ko Sung-hee]] as Shin Ja-young; Yoon-Bok\u2019s birth mother\n* [[Son Seok-koo]] as Seol-ak; Ja-young\u2019s boyfriend\n* {{ill|Jo Han-chul|ko|\uc870\ud55c\ucca0 (\ubc30\uc6b0)}} as Chang-geun\n\n====People around Young-sin====\n* [[Jeon Hye-jin (actress, born 1988)|Jeon Hye-jin]] as Yi-jin; Soo-Jin\u2019s younger sister\n* [[Go Bo-gyeol]] as Hyun-jin; Soo-jin\u2019s youngest sister\n* {{ill|Lee Jung-yeol|ko|\uc774\uc815\uc5f4 (\ubc30\uc6b0)}} as Detective Jae-beom\n*Lee Joo-Won as Tae-hoon; Yi-jin\u2019s son; Tae-mi\u2019s twin brother\n*Choi Yoo-Ri as Tae-mi; Yi-jin\u2019s daughter; Tae-hoon\u2019s twin sister \n\n==Production==\n* Child actress Heo Yool was selected out of 400 candidates for the role of Kim Hye-na.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Park|first1=Gwi-im|url=http://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=213&aid=0000999583|title=[\ub2e8\ub3c5] \ud5c8\uc728, 400\ub3001 \ub6ab\uace0 tvN '\ub9c8\ub354' \uce90\uc2a4\ud305\u2026\uc774\ubcf4\uc601\uacfc \ud22c\ud1b1|website=Naver|publisher=TV Report|accessdate=December 14, 2017|language=ko}}</ref>\n* The first four-hour script reading of the cast was held on November 1, 2017 at [[Studio Dragon]]'s main office in [[Sangam-dong]].<ref>{{cite news|last1=Jeong|first1=Yoo-na|url=http://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=076&aid=0003183100|script-title=ko:'\ub9c8\ub354' \uc774\ubcf4\uc601\u00b7\uc774\ud61c\uc601\u00b7\uace0\uc131\ud76c\u00b7\uc774\uc7ac\uc724, \uac10\ub3d9\uc758 \ub300\ubcf8\ub9ac\ub529 \ud604\uc7a5|website=Naver|publisher=Sports Chosun|accessdate=December 14, 2017|language=ko}}</ref><ref>{{cite video|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=RNUK434HyBY|title=Mother (\uba54\uc774\ud0b9) \ub300\ubcf8\ub9ac\ub529 \ub9cc\uc73c\ub85c\ub3c4 \ubab0\uc785\ub3c4 100%! tvN \uc0c8 \uc218\ubaa9\ub4dc\ub77c\ub9c8 \ub9c8\ub354 170124 EP.1|website=YouTube|publisher=tvN Drama|accessdate=January 1, 2018|language=ko}}</ref>\n\n==Original soundtrack==\n===Part 1===\n{{Track listing\n| all_writing = \n| extra_column = Artist\n| title1 = To You\n| note1 = {{lang|ko|\ub098\uc778 \ub108\uc5d0\uac8c}}\n| length1 = 04:14\n| lyrics1 = [[Tei (singer)|Tei]]\n| music1 = 1601\n| extra1 = [[Kim Yoon-ah]]\n| title2 = To You (Inst.)\n| note2 = {{lang|ko|\ub098\uc778 \ub108\uc5d0\uac8c (Inst.)}}\n| length2 = 04:14\n| music2 = 1601\n| total_length = 08:28\n}}\n\n===Part 2===\n{{Track listing\n| all_writing = \n| extra_column = Artist\n| title1 = Next To You\n| note1 = \n| length1 = 03:15\n| lyrics1 = Peter Han\n| music1 = Park Woo-sang\n| extra1 = Peter Han\n| title2 = Next To You (Inst.)\n| note2 = \n| length2 = 03:15\n| music2 = Park Woo-sang\n| total_length = 06: