BS]], [[Munhwa Broadcasting Corporation|MBC]] and [[Educational Broadcasting System|EBS]]).''}}\n\n== Awards and nominations ==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders sortable\" \n! scope=\"col\" |Award\n! scope=\"col\" |Category\n! scope=\"col\" |Recipients\n! scope=\"col\" |Result\n! scope=\"col\" |Ref\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" |1st Cannes International Series Festival \n| Best Series ||rowspan=2|''Mother''||{{nom}}|| <ref>{{cite web|url=http://english.yonhapnews.co.kr/news/2018/03/14/0200000000AEN20180314003600315.html|title=TvN's 'Mother' invited to compete in Canneseries TV festival|date=March 14, 2018|website=Yonhap News Agency}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2018/tv/news/canneseries-unveils-full-lineup-for-inaugural-edition-1202724476/|title=Canneseries Unveils Competition Lineup for Inaugural Edition|date=March 13, 2018|website=Variety}}</ref>\n|- \n! scope=\"row\" rowspan=5|[[54th Baeksang Arts Awards]]\n| [[Baeksang Arts Awards for Best Drama|  Best Drama]] ||{{won}}||rowspan=5|<ref>{{cite web|url=http://koreajoongangdaily.joins.com/news/article/article.aspx?aid=3047756&cloc=joongangdaily|title='1987' shines at Baeksang awards : The annual ceremony honors the best works in local film and television|date=May 5, 2018|website=Korea JoongAng Daily}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.jtbc.joins.com/html/136/NB11615136.html|title=\uc81c54\ud68c \ubc31\uc0c1\uc608\uc220\ub300\uc0c1, TV\u00b7\uc601\ud654 \uac01 \ubd80\ubb38\ubcc4 \uc218\uc0c1 \ud6c4\ubcf4\uc790 \uacf5\uac1c|date=April 6, 2018|website=JTBC|language=ko}}</ref> \n|-\n| [[Baeksang Arts Awards for Best Director (TV)| Best Director]] || Kim Cheol-kyu||{{nom}}\n|- \n| [[Baeksang Arts Awards for Best Actress (TV)| Best Actress]] || [[Lee Bo-young]] ||{{nom}}\n|- \n| [[Baeksang Arts Awards for Best Screenplay (TV)| Best Screenplay]] ||Jang Seo-kyung||{{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Baeksang Arts Awards for Best New Actress (TV)| Best New Actress]] || [[Heo Yool]] ||{{won}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" rowspan=2|13th 