ublisher=The Broadway League|accessdate=February 20, 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n| scope=\"row\"| Nov 14, 1932\n|Nov 1932\n|''Dear Jane''\n|Dr. Samuel Johnson\n|Civic Repertory Theatre\n|Written by Eleanor Holmes Hinkley\n|<ref>{{cite web|title=Dear Jane|url=http://www.ibdb.com/production.php?id=11672|website=IBDB|publisher=The Broadway League|accessdate=February 20, 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n| scope=\"row\"| Dec 12, 1932\n|Dec 1933\n|''Alice in Wonderland''\n|Cook, White Knight\n|Civic Repertory Theatre\n|Based on the [[Lewis Carroll]] books; written by [[Florida Friebus]] and [[Eva Le Gallienne]]\n|<ref>{{cite web|title=Alice in Wonderland|url=http://www.ibdb.com/production.php?id=11693|website=IBDB|publisher=The Broadway League|accessdate=February 20, 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n| scope=\"row\"| March 6, 1933\n|April 1933\n|{{sort|Cherry|''[[The Cherry Orchard]]''}}\n|Stationmaster\n|[[New Amsterdam Theatre]]\n|Written by [[Anton Chekhov]]; translation by [[Constance Garnett]]\n|<ref>{{cite web|title=The Cherry Orchard|url=http://www.ibdb.com/production.php?id=11735|website=IBDB|publisher=The Broadway League|accessdate=February 20, 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n| scope=\"row\"| Dec 10, 1934\n|Mar 1935\n|''Sailors of Cattaro''\n|Sepp Kriz\n|Civic Repertory Theatre\n|From the 1930 German work ''Die Matrosen von Cattaro'' by [[Friedrich Wolf (writer)|Friedrich Wolf]]; translation by Keen Wallis; adaptation by [[Michael Blankfort]]\n|<ref>{{cite web|title=Sailors of Cattaro|url=http://www.ibdb.com/production.php?id=10433|website=IBDB|publisher=The Broadway League|accessdate=February 20, 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n| scope=\"row\"| Mar 20, 1935\n|June 1935\n|''Black Pitt''\n|Hansy McCulloh\n|Civic Repertory Theatre\n|Written by [[Albert Maltz]]\n|<ref>{{cite web|title=Black Pitt|url=http://www.ibdb.com/production.php?id=9725|website=IBDB|publisher=The Broadway League|accessdate=February 20, 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n| scope=\"row\"| Nov 4, 1937\n|June 1938\n|''[[Golden Boy (play)|Golden Boy]]''\n|Lewis\n|[[Belasco Theatre]]\